{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014yV3qKWyMUY5ov9nZupF5F","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Office Agent Workflow Architecture\n     2→\n     3→## Overview\n     4→\n     5→The Office Agent workflow lives in `workflows/office-agent/` and connects to a remote Python-based Docker container service called **OfficePy** (hosted at `*.officepy.microsoftusercontent.com`).\n     6→\n     7→## Workflows\n     8→\n     9→### OfficeAgent (Sync)\n    10→- **File:** `src/office-agent-workflow.ts`\n    11→- Lightweight — sends an initial UI card annotation and completes immediately.\n    12→- Does **NOT** connect to the Docker container.\n    13→\n    14→### OfficeAgentAsync (Async)\n    15→- **File:** `src/office-agent-async-workflow.ts`\n    16→- The real orchestrator. Stateful (23hr expiry), manages per-conversation `OfficeAgentHandler` instances protected by Mutex.\n    17→- Handles warmup, input message processing, cancellation, metering, and dynamic evaluation.\n    18→\n    19→## Connection Chain\n    20→\n    21→```\n    22→OfficeAgentAsyncWorkflowLambda\n    23→  → OfficeAgentHandler              (utils/office-agent/src/office-agent.ts)\n    24→    → DocumentGenerationService     (utils/office-agent/src/service/document-generation-service.ts)\n    25→      → OfficePyClient              (utils/office-agent/src/client/officepy-client.ts)\n    26→        → OfficePy Docker Container (remote service)\n    27→```\n    28→\n    29→## How OfficePyClient Connects to the Container\n    30→\n    31→1. Reads `officePyServiceEndpointUrl` from settings (PPE/MSIT/Prod URLs, or `localhost:6010` for local dev).\n    32→2. POSTs to the generic URL to get a cluster-specific container URL: `{clusterUrl}/api/environments/a1.{containerId}/ext/`.\n    33→3. Opens a **WebSocket** to `{baseUrl}/ws` with auth headers as sub-protocol (`x-ms-proxy#...`).\n    34→4. Sends a `SessionInit` message with:\n    35→   - Agent settings and feature flags\n    36→   - Agent ID (`create-agent` for Claude Sonnet, `create-agent-gpt` for GPT-5)\n    37→   - Client metadata (app name, platform, agent name)\n    38→   - MCP server definitions\n    39→5. Container responds with `SessionInitResponse` containing `containerInstanceId` and `officeAgentVersion`.\n    40→6. Communication uses both:\n    41→   - **WebSocket**: Streaming messages, document generation\n    42→   - **HTTP**: Ping keep-alive every 60s, file download, `generateDocument` POST\n    43→\n    44→## Key Architectural Details\n    45→\n    46→- The AugLoop workflow (TypeScript/Node.js) is an **orchestrator/proxy**. It handles auth, licensing, and provides callback services that the container requests via WebSocket messages.\n    47→- Container URLs are cached in **SDS** (Shared Data Service) for multi-turn conversation reuse.\n    48→- Message handlers in `utils/office-agent/src/service/handlers/` process container callback requests:\n    49→  - Web search, enterprise file/email/calendar/chat/meeting/people/transcript fetch\n    50→  - Citation injection, chat history, agent state, query status, telemetry\n    51→- Settings are in `utils/office-agent/src/settings.ts` and `utils/office-agent/src/settings.json`.\n    52→- The `@officeagent/message-protocol` package defines the WebSocket message types shared between AugLoop and the container.\n    53→- `DocumentGenerationService` uses a **strategy pattern** (`CreateAgentDocumentGenerationStrategy`) and handles document upload to OneDrive after generation.\n    54→- The `agents/office-agent/` directory contains M365 declarative agent packaging (Teams app manifest), **not** the container code itself.\n    55→\n    56→## Environment URLs\n    57→\n    58→| Environment | URL |\n    59→|---|---|\n    60→| PPE (dev/test/int/dogfood) | `https://officeagentppe.officepy.microsoftusercontent.com` |\n    61→| MSIT | `https://officeagentmsit.officepy.microsoftusercontent.com` |\n    62→| Prod | `https://officeagent.officepy.microsoftusercontent.com` |\n    63→| Local dev | `http://localhost:6010/` |\n    64→\n    65→## Key Files\n    66→\n    67→| File | Purpose |\n    68→|---|---|\n    69→| `workflows/office-agent/src/office-agent-workflow.ts` | Sync workflow (UI card placeholder) |\n    70→| `workflows/office-agent/src/office-agent-async-workflow.ts` | Async workflow (main orchestrator) |\n    71→| `utils/office-agent/src/office-agent.ts` | `OfficeAgentHandler` — per-conversation handler |\n    72→| `utils/office-agent/src/service/document-generation-service.ts` | Document generation orchestration |\n    73→| `utils/office-agent/src/client/officepy-client.ts` | WebSocket/HTTP client to OfficePy container |\n    74→| `utils/office-agent/src/service/messenger.ts` | `WebSocketMessenger` implementation |\n    75→| `utils/office-agent/src/settings.ts` | Runtime settings definitions |\n    76→| `utils/office-agent/src/settings.json` | Environment-specific setting values |\n    77→| `utils/office-agent/src/service/handlers/` | Message handlers for container callbacks |\n    78→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JUCvAHSXRtjX93sY9sKE3i","session_id":"d982c5f4-98da-4461-b748-c7175dcade88","uuid":"020a6961-c476-41dc-aaab-26f261eb6c30"}
