{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AHaoywwTe2SSVMipqPJ8s3","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# AugLoop Connection Reliability\n     2→\n     3→**You can also see all existing (New and Active) QoS Bugs here:** [https://office.visualstudio.com/OC/\\_queries?tempQueryId=9b97fd10-3874-4d99-8975-fb7f178eb77a](https://office.visualstudio.com/OC/_queries?tempQueryId=9b97fd10-3874-4d99-8975-fb7f178eb77a)\n     4→\n     5→1. This alert indicates that we failed to connect to Augmentation Loop services. Services, such as, Proofing and Entity recognition will stop working.\n     6→2. One way to test this quickly is to open <https://fluidpreview.office.net/> and typing a spelling error. If the spelling squiggle doesn't show up after a couple of seconds, there is an issue with the connection.\n     7→3. You can run this query to find errors:\n     8→\n     9→    ```kusto\n    10→    Office_Fluid_AugLoop_Error\n    11→    | where Event_Time > ago(1h)\n    12→    | where Data_eventName == 'ActivateAugLoopAnnotationsError'\n    13→    ```\n    14→\n    15→4. You can check the ICM team for Augmentation Loop to see if there are any ongoing incidents:\n    16→\n    17→    Augmentation Loop/Triage\n    18→\n    19→5. Contacts for Augmentation Loop integration:\n    20→    1. FFX team: madosal\n    21→    2. AugLoop: rydorson\n    22→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JUCvAHSXRtjX93sY9sKE3i","session_id":"d982c5f4-98da-4461-b748-c7175dcade88","uuid":"035c1b40-fbc2-4acc-a9aa-cfe4af42ac13"}
