{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XkFiJ236tWAUQxpmxnwaxM","type":"tool_result","content":"C:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/grounding/node_modules/@types/uuid/index.d.ts\nC:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/grounding/src/api/grounding-client.ts\nC:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/grounding/src/api/grounding-http-server.ts\nC:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/grounding/src/api/grounding-service-types.ts\nC:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/grounding/src/api/index.ts\nC:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/grounding/src/base-postprocessor.ts\nC:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/grounding/src/base-preprocessor.ts\nC:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/grounding/src/base-retriever.ts\nC:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/grounding/src/base-storage.ts\nC:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/grounding/src/enterprise/index.ts\nC:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/grounding/src/enterprise/orchestration/fetch-orchestrator-factory.ts\nC:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/grounding/src/enterprise/orchestration/index.ts\nC:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/grounding/src/enterprise/orchestration/search-orchestrator-factory.ts\nC:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/grounding/src/enterprise/orchestration/user-context-orchestrator-factory.ts\nC:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/grounding/src/enterprise/postprocessing/channel-fetch-postprocessor.ts","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01TKCt5XCBDve7zLFaUYAVs5","session_id":"d982c5f4-98da-4461-b748-c7175dcade88","uuid":"af7d9365-fbe1-498a-aed3-03408b913c0a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XDR46RKSKhGcnpHTnGSSuH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Loop Components Manifest - Host Developers Guide\n     2→\n     3→[Loop Components Manifest](https://office.visualstudio.com/OC/_git/office-bohemia?path=/packages/generic-loader-manifest/README.md&_a=preview&anchor=introduction) describes each Loop Component in the [Loop Components Catalog](../partners/Components%20Catalog/index.md). The manifest contains creation data and url unfurling patterns for all supported Loop components. It also contains the settings which control the roll out of the components. The manifest is live and updated on Loop CDN, enabling all platform apps (e.g. Mobile) to easily stay up to date with the growing ecosystem.\n     4→\n     5→Loop Hosts MAY want to integrate more components in the [Loop Components Catalog](../partners/Components%20Catalog/index.md) in a generic way, leveraging the [Loop Components Manifest](../partners/Components%20Catalog/LoopComponentsManifest.md). The guide shows how to download, parse and cache the manifest efficiently, once per host session.\n     6→\n     7→This is the host developers guide. For component developers documentation, see [Loop Components Manifest - Component Developers Guide](../partners/Components%20Catalog/LoopComponentsManifest.md).\n     8→\n     9→## Usage\n    10→\n    11→## Prerequisites\n    12→\n    13→Prerequisites for Host apps who want load the Loop Components manifest to hydrate non-Fluid components.\n    14→\n    15→+ Add required CSP rules for Loop components in your host HTML pages, as listed in the [Loop Component Catalog](https://eng.ms/docs/experiences-devices/opg/office-shared/loop-experiences/loop-experiences/loop-experiences-ffx-docs/docs/partner-guide/hosting/csprules).\n    16→+ Request for [Graph Service Provisioning API](https://eng.ms/docs/experiences-devices/opg/office-shared/loop-experiences/loop-experiences/loop-experiences-ffx-docs/docs/developer-guide/dependencies/msgraph/serviceprovisioning) pre-authorization, including the TaskSet permission. This is needed to support vanity domains for Sharepoint-backed components, e.g. WXP, Video, PDF, etc.\n    17→+ Request for [OCPS](https://eng.ms/docs/experiences-devices/opg/office-shared/loop-experiences/loop-experiences/loop-experiences-ffx-docs/docs/developer-guide/dependencies/ocps) pre-authorization. This permission is needed to support enabling or disabling components via OCPS by tenant admins.\n    18→\n    19→### Supported Loop Components\n    20→\n    21→Hosts MAY pick and choose which Loop Components to support and when to roll out, by evaluating each component documentation in the [Loop Components Catalog](../partners/Components%20Catalog/index.md) and further restricting the url pattern matched registration identifiers to their own select set.\n    22→\n    23→For each of their supported registrationId, Hosts MUST install a code loader from the catalog documentation and inject them to the [Loop Loader](../hosting/index.md#host-sdk-aka-loop-loader) per [How to use Injected Dependencies](../hosting/index.md#how-to-use-injected-dependencies).\n    24→\n    25→### Load and parse the manifest\n    26→\n    27→Hosts SHOULD consume the [Loop Components Manifest](../../../packages/generic-loader-manifest/README.md) to discover all component URL patterns and create new configurations.\n    28→\n    29→To load and parse the manifest, call the [loadLoopComponentsManifestIncremental()](../../../packages/loop-component-manifest-loader/src/ComponentManifest/loadLoopComponentsManifestIncremental.ts) function from `loop-component-loader-manifest` package:\n    30→\n    31→```ts\n    32→function* loadLoopComponentsManifestIncremental(\n    33→  environment: Environment,\n    34→  dependencySynthesizer: IFluidDependencySynthesizer,\n    35→  dynamicUrlCacheHandler: DynamicUrlServiceCacheHandler,\n    36→  supportedComponentRegistrationIds?: string[],\n    37→  blockedComponentRegistrationIds?: string[]\n    38→): AsyncGenerator<LoopComponentManifestData>;\n    39→```\n    40→\n    41→+ `environment` parameter\n    42→\n    43→    Determine the deployment ring from which the manifest is downloaded.\n    44→\n    45→+ `dependencySynthesizer` parameter\n    46→\n    47→    Callers are required to pass in a number of providers. The required providers are specified by [`LoadManifestRequiredDependencies`](https://office.visualstudio.com/OC/_git/office-bohemia?path=/packages/loop-component-manifest-loader/src/ComponentManifest/types.ts&version=GBmaster&line=132&lineEnd=132&lineStartColumn=13&lineEndColumn=45&lineStyle=plain&_a=contents) type, and optional providers are specified by [`LoadManifestOptionalDependencies`](https://office.visualstudio.com/OC/_git/office-bohemia?path=/packages/loop-component-manifest-loader/src/ComponentManifest/types.ts&version=GBmaster&line=124&lineEnd=124&lineStartColumn=13&lineEndColumn=45&lineStyle=plain&_a=contents).\n    48→\n    49→> [!NOTE]\n    50→> At the time of this writing, the `OfficePolicyProvider` dependency is optional in order to avoid breaking existing hosts. However, it will be made mandatory in the next major OWH bump.\n    51→\n    52→+ `dynamicUrlCacheHandler` parameter\n    53→\n    54→    Some Chapter 3 components want to retrieve the list of urls dynamically via some service APIs. For example, **graph-loop** and **card-loop** want to call the Substrate (3S) /userconfig endpoint. Or **video** and **wxp-embed** want to call the Graph Service Provisioning endpoint to retrieve the list of vanity domains. These components indicate this intention in the manifest via the `fetchUrlsService` attribute. At the moment, we support two types of dynamic url services: `substrate` and `odsp`. Here's an excerpt from the manifest for the **graph-loop** and **video** components:\n    55→\n    56→   ```json\n    57→    {\n    58→      registrationId: '@1js/graph-loop',\n    59→      urlPatterns: {\n    60→        fetchUrlsService: {\n    61→          serviceType: 'substrate',\n    62→          filterData: {\n    63→            SourceType: ['FederatedSearch']\n    64→          }\n    65→        }\n    66→      }\n    67→    },\n    68→    {\n    69→      registrationId: '@fluidx/video-playback',\n    70→      urlPatterns: {\n    71→        fetchUrlsService: {\n    72→          serviceType: 'odsp'\n    73→        }\n    74→      }\n    75→    }\n    76→   ```\n    77→\n    78→    `loadLoopComponentsManifestIncremental()` internally takes care of calling the 3S or ODSP services on its own. To improve performance, we want to cache these dynamic service responses. However, it doesn't know where to cache it. Thus, the `dynamicUrlCacheHandler` parameter is for hosts to handle the caching work.\n    79→\n    80→+ `supportedComponentRegistrationIds` parameter"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JUCvAHSXRtjX93sY9sKE3i","session_id":"d982c5f4-98da-4461-b748-c7175dcade88","uuid":"ef2b1de8-68cc-49b1-acf1-8c2edf3715ad"}
