{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JUCvAHSXRtjX93sY9sKE3i","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile my comprehensive findings report.\n\n## Summary Report: Integration Patterns Analysis\n\nBased on my thorough search across both C:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent and C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia repositories, here are my findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. AugLoop Integration Patterns\n\n**Primary Integration Points:**\n- **C:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/docs/pptx/augloop-to-office-agent.md** - Main architecture document describing the AugLoop workflow connecting to the OfficePy Docker container\n- **C:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/.devtools/test-client/src/augloop-client.ts** - AugLoop client implementation (note: file location corrected path)\n- **C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/docs/oce-playbook/oce-teams/Triage-And-IM-Rotations/TSGs/TSG/AugLoop-Connection-Reliability.md** - Operational troubleshooting guide\n\n**Key Architecture:**\n- AugLoop acts as an **orchestrator/proxy** for WebSocket communication with OfficePy container\n- Uses **SharedTree DDS** for storing collaborative history (Copilot asks/responses)\n- Connection uses **WebSocket** to `{baseUrl}/ws` with auth headers as sub-protocol (`x-ms-proxy#...`)\n- Communication protocol: `@officeagent/message-protocol` defines WebSocket message types\n- Container URLs cached in **SDS** (Shared Data Service) for multi-turn reuse\n- Message handlers in `utils/office-agent/src/service/handlers/` process container callbacks\n\n---\n\n## 2. Office.js / 1JS Framework Patterns\n\n**Framework References Found:**\n- **C:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/excel-headless/src/sandbox/excel-office-js-sandbox.ts** - Office.js API integration\n- **C:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/ppt-edit-agent/src/ppt-office-js-helper.ts** - PowerPoint Office.js helper\n- **C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/patches/@1js+m365-chat-context+167.5.19.patch** - 1JS M365 chat context patches\n- **C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/packages/** - Multiple packages using `@1js/` scope (graph-loop, video, etc.)\n\n**1JS Usage:**\n- Office.js APIs used for headless Excel execution via sandbox\n- 1JS (OneJS) framework provides M365 integration components\n- Loop Components use `@1js/*` packages for M365 chat and copilot context\n- TaskPane architecture supported via Office.js initialization patterns\n\n---\n\n## 3. Loop Component Embedding Patterns\n\n**Design Documentation:**\n- **C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/docs/developer-guide/designs/20230116-Copilot-Component.md** - Core Copilot component design (LLM interaction, history, attribution)\n- **C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/docs/developer-guide/designs/20230621-Copilot-Page-Summary.md** - Page summary augmentation on Copilot\n- **C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/docs/partner-guide/hosting/LoopComponentsManifest.md** - Component manifest for host integration\n- **C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/apps/loop-app/src/Routes/Page/lazyAugLoopServiceFactoryExport.ts** - Lazy loading AugLoop service factory\n\n**Embedding Strategy:**\n- Loop Components manifest (CDN-delivered or NPM) defines component registration\n- Loop Page Container bundled with Loop App for collaborative editing\n- Components support **collapsed/minimized/expanded** modes (performance optimization)\n- Nested components (Scriptor in Copilot) use Fluid handles for real-time sync\n- Manifest-based dynamic loading via `loadLoopComponentsManifestIncremental()`\n\n---\n\n## 4. WebSocket & Real-Time Streaming Patterns\n\n**Streaming Architecture:**\n- **C:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/api/src/websocket/handlers/llm-proxy-handler.ts** - WebSocket handler for LLM streaming\n  - Implements **SSE (Server-Sent Events)** for streaming responses\n  - Message types: `LLMResponseType.Start`, `Chunk`, `Complete`, `Final`\n  - Rate limiting with 429 handling via function call queuing\n  - 60-minute request timeout, tracks pending requests\n\n**Protocol Details:**\n- WebSocket to HTTP proxy pattern\n- Stream headers: `Content-Type: text/event-stream; charset=utf-8`\n- Per-request tracking via UUID\n- Supports both streaming and non-streaming responses\n\n**Message Protocol:**\n- **C:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/message-protocol/src/types/core.ts**\n  - `Message<T>` base interface with sessionId\n  - `ResponseMessage<T>` for correlation via requestId\n  - Implements JSONRPC-style message routing\n\n---\n\n## 5. Cowork UX Integration (Active Development)\n\n**Evidence of Cowork Feature:**\n- **Worktree**: `/c/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/.claude/worktrees/dallas-add-cowork-route/`\n- Indicates active development of cowork route in Loop App\n- Integration with agent manifest types and routing\n\n**Cowork Found In:**\n- 142 files in OfficeAgent mention \"augloop\" (various contexts)\n- 79 files in office-bohemia mention \"augloop\"\n- 19 files in OfficeAgent mention \"cowork\"\n- 1 file in office-bohemia mentions \"cowork\" (pull requests metadata)\n\n---\n\n## 6. Copilot/Agent Collaboration Patterns\n\n**Copilot Architecture:**\n- **C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/packages/copilot/** - Loop Copilot component (20+ files)\n- Implements two-phase ask workflow: **initial ask** → **refining asks**\n- Stores history with Scriptor handles for collaborative editing\n- Attribution system marks LLM-generated vs. user-edited content\n- Feature gates: `copilot.enabled` flag + AI feature enablement setting\n\n**Agent Communication:**\n- **C:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/docs/WORKSPACE_AGENT_DESIGN.md** - Two-phase sub-agent architecture:\n  - **Phase 1**: Planning sub-agent (@workspace-planner) - generates structured outline\n  - **Phase 2**: Generation sub-agent (@workspace-generator) - executes plan\n- Uses **PostToolUse hooks** for incremental response streaming\n- Agents support multiple request types (chat_request, paralegal_request, marketer_request, etc.)\n\n---\n\n## 7. Design Docs & Cowork UX Specifications\n\n**Key Design Documents:**\n- **C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/docs/developer-guide/designs/** (35 design docs)\n  - 20230116-Copilot-Component.md - Core LLM interaction pattern\n  - 20230621-Copilot-Page-Summary.md - Scenario-based asks (vs. user-typed)\n  - 20230623-Recap-Component.md - Recap component for summarization\n  - No specific \"cowork\" design doc found (still in development via worktree)\n\n**Component Hosting:**\n- **C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/docs/partner-guide/hosting/** (40+ hosting docs)\n  - PackageIntegration.md - NPM 2x/day publish, CDN 2x/week\n  - HostPrerequisites.md - CSP rules, Graph Service, OCPS pre-auth\n  - LoopComponentsManifest.md - Dynamic component loading via manifest\n\n---\n\n## 8. Framework & Module Organization\n\n**Message Protocol (@officeagent/message-protocol):**\n- C:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/message-protocol/ - Shared WebSocket contract\n- Types: MessageType enum, Message/ResponseMessage interfaces\n- Supports: agents (create, grounding, ppt, workspace), apps (excel, ppt, word), grounding (web, enterprise, images)\n\n**Office Agent Infrastructure:**\n- **api module** - Express server, WebSocket routing, LLM proxy\n- **core module** - BaseAgent, logging, OfficeAgentSettingsManager\n- **grounding module** - Enterprise search (Substrate), web search, image search\n- **excel-headless module** - Headless Excel execution in Node.js sandbox\n\n---\n\n## File Path Summary (Key Files)\n\n| Pattern | Key Files |\n|---------|-----------|\n| **AugLoop** | `/OfficeAgent/docs/pptx/augloop-to-office-agent.md` |\n| **WebSocket/Streaming** | `/OfficeAgent/modules/api/src/websocket/handlers/llm-proxy-handler.ts` |\n| **Message Protocol** | `/OfficeAgent/modules/message-protocol/src/types/core.ts` |\n| **Copilot Design** | `/office-bohemia/docs/developer-guide/designs/20230116-Copilot-Component.md` |\n| **Component Embedding** | `/office-bohemia/docs/partner-guide/hosting/LoopComponentsManifest.md` |\n| **Wo