{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DLPgnTkmGzXzsDrb5HSUSt","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a final summary document based on all the exploration.\n\n## Comprehensive Office-Bohemia (Bebop) Codebase Exploration Report\n\nBased on thorough exploration of the office-bohemia repository, here's a complete analysis of the Bebop application architecture:\n\n### 1. **Root Documentation**\n- **File**: `/c/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/CLAUDE.md`\n- Comprehensive monorepo guidance (~200 packages, Yarn-based, Lage orchestration)\n- Office-Bohemia is the Loop repository built on Fluid Framework for real-time collaboration\n- Architecture covers containers, components, WorkspaceComponent embedding surface for M365 hosts\n- Strict code style guidelines: no `as` assertions, use `?.` and `??`, prefer immutable data, pure React components\n- Key testing patterns: Jest with jsdom, Playwright e2e tests\n\n### 2. **Bebop Application Architecture**\n\n**Location**: `/c/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/apps/bebop/`\n\n**Stack**:\n- **Framework**: TanStack Start (React 19.2.4) with React Compiler\n- **Runtime**: Nitro server runtime with Vite bundler\n- **Routing**: File-based routes via TanStack Router (generates typed route tree)\n- **Server Functions**: `createServerFn` for type-safe RPC with Zod validation\n- **Middleware Pipeline**: Auth, locale detection, telemetry, CSP nonces, CSS inlining (in `src/start.ts`)\n\n**Key Principles** (from `apps/bebop/CONTRIBUTING.md`):\n- Feature-first organization under `src/features/<feature>/`\n- Thin routes (metadata + prefetch/ensure + render)\n- Thin server functions (validate + delegate to `server/`)\n- **State split**: TanStack Query for async/remote state, Jotai for synchronous local UI state\n- SSR with streaming, React Server Components\n- **No manual memoization** - React Compiler handles this\n\n### 3. **Cowork Route Status**\n- **Does NOT exist yet** - Not found at `apps/bebop/src/routes/_mainLayout.cowork.tsx`\n- This is a new feature to be implemented\n\n### 4. **Chat Feature Structure** (`apps/bebop/src/features/conversation/`)\n\n**Components**:\n- `/Chat/Chat.tsx` - Main orchestrator\n- `/Chat/ChatLayout.tsx` - Layout composition\n- `/Chat/ChatPrompt.tsx` - Input handling\n- `/Chat/JotaiChatPromptWrapper.tsx` - Wrapper using `useChatOrchestration` hook\n- `/Chat/JotaiTranscript.tsx` - Jotai-based transcript with `messageOrderAtom`\n- `/ConversationHistory/ConversationHistory.tsx` - Wraps `<RealtimeVoiceProvider>` with hydration hooks\n\n**Server Functions**:\n- `requestChat` - Streaming chat endpoint (POST /api/conversation)\n- `getHistory` - Load conversation history (GET /api/conversation?conversationId=)\n- `detectIntent` - Intent detection\n- `warmupConversation` - Sydney client warmup\n\n**Streaming Pipeline** (`getSydneyStream.ts`):\n- Handles Sydney response mapping via `createSydneyResponseMapper`\n- Markdown parsing with `makeMarkdownToHtmlParser` from `bebop-response-parser`\n- Emits HTML + mutations via `emitResultToStream`\n- Tracks performance spans: `waiting_for_sydney`, `sydney_searching_and_reasoning`, `parser_buffering_markdown`, `streaming_chunks`\n- Manages `writeAtCursor` for incremental parsing\n- Warm Sydney client optimization with caching\n\n### 5. **Backend Communication**\n\n**API Layer Structure**:\n- **Routes**: `apps/bebop/src/routes/api/`\n  - `conversation.ts` - GET/POST handlers streaming HTML responses\n  - `chat/` - Specialized chat handlers\n- **Services** (`packages/bebop-services/`):\n  - `conversation/getConversation()`\n  - `chats/getChats()`, `deleteChats()`, `renameChat()`, `searchChats()`\n  - `profile/` - User profile operations\n  - `workspaces/` - Workspace operations\n\n**Response Handling**:\n- `bebop-response-mapping` - Maps Sydney responses to UX messages\n- `bebop-response-parser` - Incremental markdown→HTML parser with streaming mutation support\n- `bebop-conversation-orchestrator` - Streaming renderer with iframe pooling, mutation tracking, telemetry\n\n**Streaming Contract** (`StreamingMutationTypes.ts`):\n- `MutationDescriptor` with operations: `replace | delete | append`\n- Hash-based targeting: `startHash`, `endHash`, `targetHash`, `newHash`\n- HTML mutations encoded as `<script>` tags for safe JSON serialization\n\n### 6. **Progression/CoT UI Components**\n\n**Current State**:\n- **ChainOfThoughtCard**: Does NOT exist (not implemented)\n- **ProgressionCard**: Does NOT exist (not implemented)\n- **Message Flags**: `addToChainOfThought?: boolean` exists in `MessageTypes.ts`\n- **Progress Support**: `MessageProgressType = 'None' | 'Processing' | 'Completed' | 'Error' | 'Canceled'` defined\n\n**Available Message Types** (54 total in `MessageTypes.ts`):\n- `Chat`, `Progress`, `InternalStateMarker`, `InternalActionMarker`, `InternalLoaderMessage`\n- `GeneratedCode`, `ExecuteAction`, `RenderCardRequest`, `RenderContentRequest`\n- Support for adaptive cards, source attributions, references\n\n### 7. **Voice Integration** (`RealtimeVoiceProvider` Pattern)\n\n**Location**: `/packages/bebop-ux/src/components/RealtimeVoice/`\n\n**Structure**:\n```tsx\nexport const RealtimeVoiceProvider = ({ children }: PropsWithChildren): JSX.Element => {\n  // Wraps WebRTCSessionProvider from @bebopjs/bebop-webrtc\n  // Provides Sydney token provider\n  // Handles session correlation ID\n  // Integrates with bebop-auth for token fetching\n}\n```\n\n**Dependencies**:\n- `@bebopjs/bebop-webrtc/WebRTCSessionProvider`\n- `@bebopjs/bebop-shared-config` - SYDNEY_CONFIG\n- WebRTC for real-time audio streams\n- VoiceOverlay from `/packages/bebop-ux/src/layouts/Voice/VoiceOverlay.tsx`\n\n**Voice Interaction**:\n- Atoms at `apps/bebop/src/features/input/atoms/voiceInteractionAtoms.ts`\n- VoiceOverlayDisplay component in feature\n- ClothViz visualization component\n\n### 8. **AugLoop Integration**\n\n**Status**: NO existing AugLoop or OfficeAgent references found in Bebop codebase\n\n**However**, `@1js/*` packages ARE extensively used:\n- `@1js/ac-react-fluent-ui` - Adaptive Cards UI\n- `@1js/ai-hub-telemetry`, `@1js/ai-hub-types` - AI Hub integration\n- `@1js/m365-chat-context`, `@1js/m365-chat-types` - M365 chat context\n- `@1js/scc-service-voice-realtime-augloop` - AugLoop voice service (in audio-player package)\n\n### 9. **1JS Framework Integration**\n\n**Integration Points**:\n- Adaptive Cards: `@1js/ac-react-fluent-ui` (`packages/adaptive-card/`)\n- AI Hub: Telemetry and types\n- M365 Chat: Context and types for Teams/Outlook integration\n- Voice Realtime: `@1js/scc-service-voice-realtime-augloop` for audio streaming\n- Custom packages wrap 1JS libraries (e.g., `bebop-sydney-client`)\n\n**Office Extensibility**:\n- No explicit Office.js or Office Add-in patterns found yet\n- Architecture supports embedding via `WorkspaceComponent` (from Loop design)\n- Ready for Teams, Outlook, Word, Loop App hosts\n\n### 10. **Intent Detection Integration**\n\n**Location**: `apps/bebop/src/features/intentDetection/`\n\n**Current Implementation**:\n- Simple keyword-matching rules in `intentDetector.ts`\n- Detects: `image_generation` (Designer), `research` (Researcher), `analysis` (Analyst), `presentation` (PowerPoint), `document` (Word), `spreadsheet` (Excel), `code` (Coder)\n- Server function: `detectIntentServerFn` using Zod validation\n- Exported atoms in `bebop-ux`: `detectedIntentAtom`, `refinerSelectionsAtom`, `clearRefinerSelectionsAtom`\n- Types: `AgentType`, `DetectIntentResponse`, `DetectedIntent`, `IntentType`\n\n**Integration Path**: Ready for agent/orchestrator routing based on detected intent\n\n### 11. **Message State Management**\n\n**Jotai Atoms** (`packages/bebop-ux/src/atoms/messageAtoms.ts`):\n- `messageOrderAtom` - Message rendering order\n- `addMessagesAtom` - Batch add messages\n- `updateMessageAtom` - Per-message updates (via atomFamily)\n- `hasMessagesAtom` - Boolean flag\n- `resetMessagesAtom` - Clear all messages\n- `conversationIdAtom` - Current conversation context\n\n**Chat Orchestration** (`useChatOrchestration` hook):\n- Manages `SubmitPromptParameters` (prompt, attachments, selectedText, queryAnnotations, clientRequestId)\n- Creates MessageEntry objects with status (`pending | complete`)\n- Persona tracking (`user | bot`)\n- Attachment handling (local uploads + pasted files)\n- AbortController for request cancellation\n\n### 12. **Telemetry & Performance**\n\n**Core Infrastructure** (`src/core/telemetry/`):\n- `PerfTracker` interface for event marking\n- Performance spans: `waiting_for_sydney`, `searching_and_reasoning`, `parser_buffering`, `streaming_chunks`\n- Web Vitals tracking hooks\n- OneDS integration via `bebop-telemetry` (fields must match schema or silently dropped)\n- Server metrics emission in streaming response\n\n**Trace Results**:\n- Emitted via `emitTraceResults()` at stream completion\n- Includes timing data from `SimpleTracer` spans\n\n### 13. **Key Package Exports** (`bebop-ux/index.ts`)\n\n**Chat Components**:\n- `ChatMessage`, `ChatResponse` (lazy), `RealtimeVoiceProvider`, `VoiceButton`\n- `useChatOrchestration` - Main orchestration hook\n- `useConversationPerfTracker` - Performance tracking\n- `useHydrateMessages` - Initialize messages from server\n\n**Streaming Utilities** (from `bebop-conversation-orchestrator`):\n- `parseMutationTemplate`, `applyMutation` - DOM mutation handling\n- `encodeJsonScriptTag`, `parseJsonScript` - Serialization\n\n**Intent Detection**:\n- `detectedIntentAtom`, `refinerSelectionsAtom`, `agentType` enums\n\n### 14. **Existing Routes** (`apps/bebop/src/routes/`)\n\n- `_mainLayout.index.tsx` - Home\n- `_mainLayout.conversation.$conversationId.tsx` - Single conversation view\n- `_mainLayout.conversations/` - List of conversations\n- `_mainLayout.agents.tsx` - Agents store (ComingSoon)\n- `_mainLayout.search.tsx` - Search\n- `_mainLayout.workspaces.tsx`, `_mainLayout.workspace.$workspaceId.tsx` - Workspaces\n- `/api/conversation` - REST endpoint (GET/POST streaming)\n- `/demos/*` - Demo routes\n- `/measure/*` - Performance measurement routes\n\n### 15. **Architecture Compliance Rules**\n\n**Dependency Flow**:\n```\nroutes → features/components|queries|mutations\nfeatures/components → features/queries|mutations|hooks|atoms\nfeatures/hooks → features/queries|mutations|atoms\nfeatures/queries → features/serverFunctions\nfeatures/mutations → features/serverFunctions\nfeatures/serverFunctions → features/server → external services\nfeatures → core|shared (allowed)\nshared → core (allowed)\ncore → features (NOT allowed)\nshared → features (NOT allowed)\nfeatures/client ↔ features/server (NO cross-imports)\n```\n\n**Code Style**:\n- Use `useId()` for accessible IDs\n- No `useEffect` for derived state\n- Group related state: `useState({ x: 0, y: 0 })`\n- Status enums over booleans: `'loading' | 'error' | 'success'`\n- Async/await preferred, no `setTimeout` workarounds\n- Use logger instance, never `console.log`\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Ready Integration Points\n\n1. **Agent/Orchestrator Ready**: Intent detection atoms + message routing infrastructure exists\n2. **Streaming Pipeline Ready**: Full chain from Sydney response → parser → mutations → streaming\n3. **Voice Ready**: RealtimeVoiceProvider pattern, WebRTC integration, correlation IDs\n4. **State Management Ready**: Jotai atoms for message state, TanStack Query for async operations\n5. **Telemetry Ready**: PerfTracker, Web Vitals, span-based tracing with OneDS\n6. **API Layer Ready**: REST endpoints, server functions, auth context injection\n7. **1JS Integration**: Adaptive Cards, AI Hub, M365 Chat contexts already in place\n\n### Features NOT Yet Implemented\n\n1. **Cowork Route** - Placeholder needed\n2. **ChainOfThoughtCard** - UI component not created\n3. **ProgressionCard** - UI component not created\n4. **Agent Handlers** - Intent routing to actual agents incomplete\n5. **AugLoop Service Binding** - Voice service available but not integrated into flow\n6. **OfficeAgent References** - No current integration points"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a8d52587aafcdabf1 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 87105\ntool_uses: 58\nduration_ms: 412563</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d982c5f4-98da-4461-b748-c7175dcade88","uuid":"ddc3b195-847e-4958-836e-988418dc80f5","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the office-bohemia (Bebop) codebase at C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia. I need to understand:\n\n1. Read CLAUDE.md at the root if it exists\n2. The cowork route that was recently added: apps/bebop/src/routes/_mainLayout.cowork.tsx\n3. The existing Chat feature structure under apps/bebop/src/features/\n4. How Bebop communicates with backend services (API layer, SSE/streaming)\n5. The progression/CoT UI components (ChainOfThoughtCard, ProgressionCard)\n6. Any existing AugLoop integration - search for \"augloop\" or \"AugLoop\"\n7. How Bebop currently connects to agents/orchestrators\n8. The 1JS framework integration - search for \"1js\" or \"oneJS\" or references to Office extensibility\n9. The RealtimeVoiceProvider pattern\n10. Any existing OfficeAgent references in the Bebop codebase\n\nBe very thorough - I need actual file contents and patterns, not just file listings.","agentId":"a8d52587aafcdabf1","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a final summary document based on all the exploration.\n\n## Comprehensive Office-Bohemia (Bebop) Codebase Exploration Report\n\nBased on thorough exploration of the office-bohemia repository, here's a complete analysis of the Bebop application architecture:\n\n### 1. **Root Documentation**\n- **File**: `/c/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/CLAUDE.md`\n- Comprehensive monorepo guidance (~200 packages, Yarn-based, Lage orchestration)\n- Office-Bohemia is the Loop