{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FtHTxqGkvHjDXUreT7KeJ6","type":"tool_result","content":"# Office Agent\n\nAgent in a container, built for Office scenarios.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- **[Node.js](https://nodejs.org/en) >= v20** — recommend using [nvm-windows](https://github.com/coreybutler/nvm-windows) (with `nvm install lts`)\n- **[Python](https://www.python.org/downloads/) >= 3.8** — for evaluation framework and testing tools (Python 3.12 recommended for msal[broker] support)\n- **[.NET SDK](https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download) >= 8.0.416** — required by global.json\n- [**Docker Desktop**](https://docs.docker.com/desktop/setup/install/windows-install/)\n- [**Visual Studio Code**](https://code.visualstudio.com/)\n\n## Quick Start\n\n> **Note**: Only Node.js and Python are required upfront. All other tools are installed automatically.\n\nRun the automated setup to configure your development environment:\n\n```bash\nnpm run setup\n```\n\nThis will:\n- Install global tools (Yarn, vsts-npm-auth)\n- Install Node.js dependencies\n- Create Python virtual environment and install packages\n- Install VS Code extensions (ESLint, EditorConfig, Python)\n- Configure Git settings\n\n> **Python Note**: VS Code automatically detects the `./venv` virtual environment. For terminal Python work, activate it with `.\\venv\\Scripts\\Activate.ps1` (Windows) or `source venv/bin/activate` (Mac/Linux).\n\n### Build\n\n> **Warning**: Docker Desktop must be running before executing `yarn build`. The build will fail if Docker is stopped.\n\n```bash\nyarn build\n```\n\n### Test\n```bash\nyarn test               # Runs both Jest (TypeScript/JavaScript) and pytest (Python) tests\n```\n\nTests include:\n- **Jest**: TypeScript/JavaScript unit tests with coverage\n- **pytest**: Python unit tests with coverage (see [Python Testing](docs/PYTHON_TESTING.md))\n- Coverage reports generated only in CI/CD (when `TF_BUILD` is set)\n\n### Run\n\nStart the Docker container:\n\n```bash\nyarn start              # Start Docker container and test client (no AugLoop required)\n```\n\nStart the Docker Compose\n```bash\nyarn start:compose\n```\n\nStop the Docker container:\n\n```bash\nyarn stop               # Stops and removes the OfficeAgent1 container\n```\n\nSee the [Available Scripts](#available-scripts) section for the complete list of Docker operations.\n\n## Development\n\n### Hot Reload\n\nFor faster iteration during development, use hot reload to deploy code changes without rebuilding the Docker image:\n\n```bash\nyarn reload             # Build your code changes and copy built files to running container and restart\n```\n\nThis updates `api/dist/` and `skills/` in the running container in seconds instead of minutes.\n\n> **Note**: If you modify Dockerfile, package.json dependencies, or other infrastructure files, run `yarn build` to rebuild the full Docker image.\n\n### Smoke Tests\n\n```bash\n# Health check\noagent ping\n\n# Generate a document (this will take a while)\noagent generate \"Create a simple document about cats\" -o ./myfile.docx\n```\n\nFor direct API testing, you can use curl:\n\n```bash\n# Health check\ncurl http://localhost:6010/health","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01TKCt5XCBDve7zLFaUYAVs5","session_id":"d982c5f4-98da-4461-b748-c7175dcade88","uuid":"d4a32a35-0ced-486e-813c-11c940a20c2a"}
