{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TKCt5XCBDve7zLFaUYAVs5","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive information. Let me create a detailed summary document for the user:\n\n## Comprehensive OfficeAgent Codebase Exploration Report\n\nI've conducted a thorough exploration of the OfficeAgent monorepo. Here's a detailed analysis of the architecture:\n\n---\n\n### 1. REPOSITORY STRUCTURE & OVERVIEW\n\n**Root Files:**\n- `/CLAUDE.md` - Project guidelines (no 1JS framework, uses Yarn 4.10.3 + Lage task runner)\n- `/package.json` - Monorepo with Yarn workspaces: `.devtools/*`, `modules/*`, `agents/*`\n- Key tools: Claude Agent SDK 0.2.39, GitHub Copilot SDK 0.1.30, AugLoop runtime client (test-client)\n\n**Directory Layout:**\n```\nagents/                    # 16 agent implementations\n├── create-agent/         # Main DOCX/PPTX/XLSX creation agent\n├── ppt-agent/            # PowerPoint specialized\n├── excel-agent/          # Excel specialized\n├── grounding-agent/      # Searches & grounding\n├── odsp-agent/           # SharePoint/OneDrive\n└── [11 others: gpt-create-agent, dw-*, workspace-agent, office-agent]\n\nmodules/                   # Shared libraries (@officeagent/*)\n├── api/                  # Express server (port 6010) + WebSocket\n├── core/                 # BaseAgent, SessionContext, HookRegistry, logging\n├── orchestrator/         # IOrchestrator abstraction (claude + ghcp providers)\n├── chain-of-thought/     # Progress/CoT tracking & streaming\n├── grounding/            # Enterprise search, web search, image search\n├── message-protocol/     # WebSocket message types, RequestContext\n├── excel-headless/       # Cloud Excel via headless service\n├── html2pptx/            # HTML → PPTX conversion\n├── json-to-docx-ooxml/   # JSON → OOXML (Word) generation\n├── mcp-proxy/            # MCP tool integration\n└── [10+ others]\n\n.devtools/                 # Development tools\n├── cli/                  # oagent CLI tool\n├── test-client/          # Augloop test client\n├── e2e-tests/            # End-to-end testing\n└── launcher/             # Container orchestration\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. CLAUDE.md AT ROOT\n\nThe root `CLAUDE.md` provides critical context:\n- **Critical**: Use **PowerShell** for `yarn`, `oagent`, `gulp` commands (Bash will fail)\n- File searching (grep, find) works in any shell\n- All config uses `OAGENT_` prefix (`OAGENT_AGENTID`, `OAGENT_FLIGHTS`)\n- Default API: `http://localhost:6010`\n- Agents register skills, flights, filters in `src/registry.ts`\n- Logging rule: **NEVER include user data in `logInfo`/`logWarn`/`logError`** (telemetry), use `logDebug` for local data\n- Agent-specific CLAUDE.md files exist for each area (CLAUDE_EXCEL.md, CLAUDE_POWERPOINT.md, CLAUDE_WORD.md)\n\n---\n\n### 3. ORCHESTRATOR PACKAGE - IOrchestrator & ClaudeOrchestrator\n\n**Location:** `/modules/orchestrator`\n\n**Core Interface:**\n```typescript\n// IOrchestrator - unified abstraction for all AI providers\ninterface IOrchestrator {\n  run(request: OrchestratorRequest): Promise<OrchestratorResult>;\n  runStream(request: OrchestratorRequest): AsyncIterable<OrchestratorMessage>;\n  interrupt(): Promise<void>;\n}\n\n// OrchestratorRequest - what agents send to the orchestrator\ninterface OrchestratorRequest {\n  prompt: string;\n  userContext?: string;           // Injected before prompt\n  systemPrompt?: string;\n  model?: string;                 // e.g., 'claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929'\n  maxTurns?: number;\n  reasoningEffort?: 'low' | 'medium' | 'high' | 'max' | 'xhigh';\n  allowedTools?: string[];        // Tool allowlist\n  disallowedTools?: string[];     // Tool blocklist\n  toolDefinitions?: unknown[];    // For providers like GHCP\n  cwd?: string;\n  env?: Record<string, string>;\n  abortController?: AbortController;\n  hooks?: OrchestratorHooks;      // Batch mode hooks (onMessage, onError, onPre/PostToolUse)\n  toolHooks?: GenericToolHooks;   // Provider-agnostic tool interception hooks\n  sessionId?: string;             // For resuming conversations\n  providerOptions?: Record<string, unknown>;  // Provider-specific (Claude: `continue`, `stderr`, `permissionMode`)\n}\n\n// OrchestratorMessage - normalized output for all providers\ninterface OrchestratorMessage {\n  type: 'assistant' | 'tool_use' | 'tool_result' | 'thinking' | 'system' | 'result' | 'progress';\n  content?: string;\n  toolName?: string;\n  toolInput?: unknown;\n  result?: OrchestratorResult;    // Embedded when type === 'result'\n  durationMs?: number;\n  sessionId?: string;\n  raw?: unknown;                  // Provider-specific raw data\n}\n\n// OrchestratorResult - final output\ninterface OrchestratorResult {\n  content: string;\n  status: 'completed' | 'exhausted' | 'failed' | 'aborted';\n  sessionId?: string;\n  error?: string;\n  usage?: OrchestratorUsage;      // Metrics: inputTokens, outputTokens, costUsd, durationMs, turnCount\n  metadata?: Record<string, unknown>;\n}\n```\n\n**Provider Pattern:**\n- `/providers/base-orchestrator.ts` - Abstract base class; providers override `runStream()` and `interrupt()`\n- `/providers/claude-orchestrator.ts` - Claude Agent SDK adapter\n- `/providers/ghcp-orchestrator.ts` - GitHub Copilot SDK adapter (lazy-loaded)\n- Factory: `createOrchestrator('claude' | 'ghcp')` - registry-based instantiation\n\n**Hook System:**\n```typescript\n// Generic tool hooks (provider-agnostic)\ninterface GenericToolHooks {\n  preToolUse?: PreToolUseHook[];       // (toolName, input) → {continue, modifiedInput?, reason?}\n  postToolUse?: PostToolUseHook[];     // (toolName, output) → {continue, modifiedOutput?}\n  onSessionStart?: SessionHook[];\n  onSessionEnd?: SessionHook[];\n}\n```\n\n**Hook Adapter:**\n- `/hooks/claude-hook-adapter.ts` - `toClaudeHooks()` & `mergeWithClaudeHooks()` translate GenericToolHooks → Claude SDK format\n- Allows hook providers (ppt-hooks, word-hooks, excel-hooks) to be written once, work with all orchestrators\n\n---\n\n### 4. API SURFACE (Port 6010)\n\n**Location:** `/modules/api/src`\n\n**Key Endpoints:**\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |\n|----------|--------|---------|\n| `/ping` | GET | Health check (responds \"pong\") |\n| `/health` | GET | Extended health status |\n| `/test` | GET | Deep health check (Chromium headless test) |\n| `/generateDocument` | POST | Main document generation (HTTP request) |\n| `/download` | GET | File download from workspace |\n| `/upload` | POST | Binary file upload (application/octet-stream) |\n| `/logs` | GET | Fetch & clear log entries |\n| `/ws` | WebSocket | Primary message channel (JSON message + JSON-RPC 2.0) |\n\n**WebSocket Message Types:**\n- `ChatRequest` - Initiate document generation\n- `ChatResponse` - Acknowledgment\n- `TaskCompletionNotification` - Progress updates\n- `MessageAnnotation` - Query metadata (entities, filters)\n- `AgentStateRequest/Response` - State management\n- `ChatHistoryRequest/Response` - History queries\n\n**Internal Port:** 6011 (for internal handler communication, see `/routes-internal.ts`)\n\n**Request Flow (HTTP `/generateDocument`):**\n1. Client POSTs with: `userQuery`, `groundingContent`, `conversationId`, `queryAnnotations`, `webSearch`, `enterpriseSearch`, etc.\n2. Server generates `requestId` if missing, checks conversation not busy\n3. Loads agent from `AgentRegistry.getAgent(agentId)`\n4. Calls `agent.run(processedQuery, requestContext, turnNumber)`\n5. Returns: `{success, filename, filePath, requestId, conversationId}` or 202 (async)\n\n**WebSocket Flow (streamlined via `/ws`):**\n- Client connects to `/ws` (WebSocket upgrade on port 6010)\n- Sends `SessionInitMessage` → server initializes agent context\n- Sends `AgentRequestMessage` (type: ChatRequest) → routed to agent handler\n- Server streams progress via `TaskCompletionNotification`, CoT updates\n- Final response as `ChatResponseMessage`\n\n---\n\n### 5. HOW AGENTS ARE STRUCTURED\n\n**Example: CreateAgent** (`/agents/create-agent`)\n\n**Key Files:**\n```\nsrc/\n  create-agent.ts          # Main class extending BaseAgent\n  registry.ts              # AgentRegistryConfig: versions, flights, filters, skills, subagents\n  types.ts                 # AgentType enum (WordAgent, ExcelAgent, PowerPointAgent)\n  constants.ts             # Flight keys, artifact type constants\n  hooks/\n    base-hooks.ts          # BaseHooksProvider - shared hooks (perf tracking, CoT)\n    excel-hooks.ts         # ExcelHooksProvider - Excel-specific hooks\n    ppt-hooks.ts           # PowerPointHooksProvider\n    word-hooks.ts          # WordHooksProvider\n    file-observer-hooks.ts # File system monitoring\n  services/\n    performance-tracker-service.ts    # Hook-based perf metrics\n    chat-history-service.ts           # Chat history persistence\n    agent-state-service.ts            # Agent state management\n    file-watcher.ts                   # Monitor output directory changes\n    websocket-messenger.ts            # Send messages to clients\n  handlers/\n    agent-request-handler.ts          # JSON-RPC & legacy request handling\n    sydney-request-parser.ts          # AugLoop message parsing\n  prompts/<version>/\n    system-prompt.md                  # EJS template for system prompt\n    rai.md                            # Responsible AI guidelines\n    agent-capabilities/               # Per-type descriptions\n    skills/                           # Skill definitions (xlsx/, pptx/, docx/, etc.)\n    subagents/                        # Sub-agent prompts (markdown with YAML frontmatter)\n    scripts/                          # Runtime scripts deployed to workspace\n    overwrites/                       # Flight-conditional prompt replacements\n```\n\n**CreateAgent Pattern:**\n```typescript\nexport class CreateAgent extends BaseAgent {\n  private hookRegistry: HookRegistry;  // Manages hook providers for different agents\n  private requestInterceptors?: RequestInterceptors;\n  private context?: SessionContext;\n\n  constructor() {\n    super(agentRegistry);  // Pass AgentRegistryConfig\n    this.hookRegistry = new HookRegistry();\n    this.hookRegistry.register('base', new BaseHooksProvider());\n    this.hookRegistry.register(AgentType.WordAgent, new WordHooksProvider());\n    this.hookRegistry.register(AgentType.ExcelAgent, new ExcelHooksProvider());\n    this.hookRegistry.register(AgentType.PowerPointAgent, new PowerPointHooksProvider());\n  }\n\n  async initialize(context: SessionContext): Promise<void> {\n    this.resolveConfig(context);  // Apply flights & filters from settings manager\n    this.context = context;\n    // Register WebSocket handlers, initialize services\n    context.wsRouter.registerHandler(MessageType.ChatRequest, this.handleChatRequest.bind(this));\n    // Initialize JSON-RPC if enabled\n    if (this.jsonRpcEnabled) {\n      context.wsRouter.getJsonRpcRouter().registerRequestHandler(JsonRpcMethod.MessageSend, ...);\n    }\n  }\n\n  async run(userQuery: string, requestContext: RequestContext, turnNumber?: number): Promise<void> {\n    // Orchestrate document generation\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Registry Configuration** (`registry.ts` pattern):\n```typescript\nexport const agentRegistry: AgentRegistryConfig = {\n  id: 'create-agent',\n  name: 'Create Agent',\n  packageName: '@officeagent/create-agent',\n  defaultVersion: '1.0.0',\n  versions: [\n    {\n      version: '1.0.0',\n      model: 'claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929',\n      maxThinkingTokens: 1024,\n      maxTurns: 2000,\n      systemPrompt: './system-prompt.md',\n      allowedTools: ['Read', 'Write', 'Edit', 'Bash', 'Task', 'Skill', ...],\n      skills: ['docx', 'pptx', 'xlsx', 'image-search', ...],\n      subagents: ['pptx-html-creator-validator', 'docx-page-subagent', ...],\n      scripts: ['send-clarification-config.js'],\n      intentDetectionDir: ['CLARIFICATION.md', 'CHAT_REPLY.md', ...],\n    },\n    { version: '1.1.0', ... },  // New version with pipeline upgrades\n  ],\n  flights: [  // Flight-based config overrides\n    { flightKey: 'OfficeAgent.EnableCreateAgent@1.1.0', applicableVersions: ['1.1.0'], config: {...} },\n  ],\n  filters: [  // Filter rules\n    { filterKey: 'disableWebSearch', skills: ['web-search', 'web-fetch'] },\n  ],\n};\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. HOOK SYSTEM - STREAMING CoT & PROGRESSION\n\n**Location:** `/modules/chain-of-thought` + `/modules/core/src/agent/claude-hooks.ts`\n\n**Hook Provider Pattern:**\n```typescript\n// HookProvider - factory for creating hooks\nexport interface HookProvider {\n  createHooks(context: SessionContext, turnContext?: TurnContext): AgentHooks;\n}\n\nexport interface AgentHooks {\n  claude: Options['hooks'];  // Claude SDK hook structure\n  startTurn?: (turnContext: TurnContext) => Promise<void>;  // Called at turn start\n  preFileWatcherStart?: () => Promise<void>;\n}\n\n// HookRegistry - manages multiple hook providers\nexport class HookRegistry {\n  register(key: string, provider: HookProvider): void { ... }\n  getHooks(key: string, context: SessionContext, turnContext?: TurnContext): AgentHooks { ... }\n}\n```\n\n**Chain of Thought (CoT) System:**\n```typescript\n// Types from chain-of-thought/src/types.ts\ninterface ChainOfThoughtMessage {\n  type: string;  // 'assistant' | 'result'\n  message?: { content?: ChainOfThoughtContentBlock[] };\n  subtype?: string;  // 'success', 'error_max_turns', etc.\n  result?: string;\n  parent_tool_use_id?: string | null;  // Identifies sub-agent messages\n}\n\n// Manager API\ninitChainOfThought(outputDir, logDir, workspaceDir, locale, flights?, contentNotifier?);\ntrackChainOfThought(message: ChainOfThoughtMessage): Promise<void>;  // Queue message for processing\ncloseChainOfThought(): Promise<void>;  // Wait for queue completion, flush\n\n// CoT is written to `.claude/cot.jsonl` in turn directory\n// Messages are queued async, processed via FileHandler + QueueManager\n// Flights: useContentHandler, sendOnlyNewUpdates, useEnhancedHeuristics, requireToolUseForQueueFallback\n```\n\n**Example Hook (BaseHooksProvider):**\n```typescript\n// Performance tracking hook - fired before/after each tool use\nconst perfHooks = createPerfTrackingHooks(sessionId, settingsManager);\n\nconst claudeHooks: Options['hooks'] = {\n  PreToolUse: [{ hooks: [perfHooks.PreToolUse] }],\n  PostToolUse: [{ hooks: [perfHooks.PostToolUse] }],\n  SessionStart: [{ hooks: [perfHooks.SessionStart] }],\n  SessionEnd: [{ hooks: [perfHooks.SessionEnd] }],\n};\n\n// startTurn hook - called at beginning of each turn\nstartTurn: async (turnContext: TurnContext) => {\n  const turnNumber = turnContext.workspaceManager.getCurrentTurnNumber();\n  logInfo(..., `[BaseHooks] Turn ${turnNumber} started`);\n  // Copy entityMap from previous turn, fetch user attachments, etc.\n}\n```\n\n**Progression/Streaming:**\n- Hooks are Claude SDK hooks (`Options['hooks']` with PreToolUse, PostToolUse callbacks)\n- They execute in-band during agentic turns\n- CoT is tracked separately via `trackChainOfThought()` → async queued writes to `.claude/cot.jsonl`\n- WebSocket messenger sends `TaskCompletionNotification` & progress updates to client\n- No explicit \"cowork\" protocol; progression sent via individual WebSocket messages\n\n---\n\n### 7. GROUNDING PIPELINE\n\n**Location:** `/modules/grounding`\n\n**Grounding Service Types:**\n```typescript\n// Request to grounding service\ninterface GroundingHttpRequest {\n  query: string;\n  configs?: { enterpriseSearch?: boolean, webSearch?: boolean };\n  conversationId?: string;\n  sessionId?: string;\n  requestId?: string;\n  queryAnnotations?: IQueryAnnotation[];  // User-attached entities\n}\n\n// Response from grounding service\ninterface GroundingHttpResponse {\n  status: 'completed' | 'failed';\n  groundingContent: string;              // Formatted markdown\n  metadata?: { requestId, durationMs, sourcesUsed };\n  error?: string;\n}\n\n// HTTP Server (default port 7010)\nclass GroundingHttpServer { ... }  // Runs search orchestration\n\n// Client for internal agent-to-agent calls\nclass GroundingClient { ... }  // Calls local grounding service\n```\n\n**Grounding Modules:**\n- `enterprise/` - Enterprise search via orchestration (fetch, search, user-context orchestrators)\n- `images/` - Image search integration\n- `user-attachment/` - Fetch user-attached content (from provisioned files)\n- `shared/` - Shared utilities\n\n**parseGroundingContent():**\n```typescript\n// Parses grounding.md format into clarification questions, message annotations, etc.\nconst groundingContentParsed = parseGroundingContent(groundingContent);\n// Returns structured questions, annotations, and text for injection into user query\n```\n\n**Enterprise Search Orchestration:**\n- **Fetch Orchestrator** - Retrieves files from SharePoint/OneDrive\n- **Search Orchestrator** - Searches enterprise knowledge\n- **User Context Orchestrator** - Builds user profile context\n- Post-processors format results into markdown for injection\n\n---\n\n### 8. AUGLOOP INTEGRATION\n\n**Location:** `/.devtools/test-client/src/augloop-client.ts`\n\n**What is AugLoop?**\n- Microsoft's intelligent document collaboration platform\n- `@augloop/runtime-client` - Client SDK for annotations & operations\n- Test client uses it for UI annotation callbacks\n\n**AugLoopClient Pattern:**\n```typescript\nclass AugLoopClient {\n  async initialize(environment: TokenEnvironment, flights?: string): Promise<void> {\n    const runtime = createRuntime();\n    runtime?.init(endpointUrl, {\n      appName: 'OfficeAgent',\n      appPlatform: 'TestClient',\n      flights,\n      uiLanguage: 'en-US',\n    }, {\n      onAnnotationResult: (op: IOperation) => { ... }  // Callback when annotation completes\n    });\n  }\n  // Used for testing agent against AugLoop backend\n}\n```\n\n**Endpoints by Environment:**\n- Dev: `http://localhost:11040`\n- Prod: `https://augloop.svc.cloud.microsoft`\n- Gov: `https://augloop.gov.online.office365.us`\n- Gallatin: `https://augloop.microsoftonline.cn`\n\n**Integration points:**\n- Used in test-client only (not production agents)\n- Test client registers annotation callbacks, validates operations\n\n---\n\n### 9. MESSAGE PROTOCOL & WebSocket ROUTING\n\n**Location:** `/modules/message-protocol`\n\n**Core Types:**\n```typescript\n// Base message schema\ninterface Schema {\n  type: MessageType;\n  id: string;\n}\n\ninterface Message<T = unknown> extends Schema {\n  sessionId: string;\n  payload: T;\n}\n\ninterface ResponseMessage<T = unknown> extends Message<T> {\n  requestId: string;\n}\n\n// Scenario & grounding toggles\nenum ScenarioType { Consumer = 'consumer', Enterprise = 'enterprise' }\ninterface IGroundingSourceToggles {\n  webSearch: boolean;\n  enterpriseSearch: boolean;\n}\n\n// Client metadata\ninterface ClientMetadata {\n  agentName?: string;\n  userEmail?: string;\n  // ... platform-specific fields\n}\n```\n\n**WebSocket Router:**\n```typescript\n// modules/core/src/websocket/router.ts\nexport class WebSocketRouter {\n  registerHandler(messageType: string, handler: MessageHandler): void { ... }\n  async routeMessage(rawMessage: string, ws: WebSocket): Promise<void> {\n    // Parse JSON, check for JSON-RPC 2.0 (delegate to jsonRpcRouter)\n    // else route by message.type to registered handler\n  }\n  getJsonRpcRouter(): JsonRpcRouter { ... }\n}\n\n// Message handler signature\ntype MessageHandler = (message: any, ws: WebSocket) => boolean | Promise<boolean>;\n```\n\n**JSON-RPC 2.0 Support:**\n- `isJsonRpcMessage(message)` - checks for `jsonrpc: \"2.0\"` + `method`\n- `JsonRpcRouter` - handles `method`, `id`, `params` format\n- Enables unified request-response pattern for message types\n\n---\n\n### 10. FRONTEND COMMUNICATION PATTERNS\n\n**Session Initialization Flow:**\n1. Client connects WebSocket to `/ws`\n2. Sends `SessionInitMessage` with client metadata, grounding toggles, MCP configs\n3. Server calls `registerSessionInitHandler()` → initializes agents in `AgentRegistry`\n4. Agent's `initialize(context: SessionContext)` called\n5. `SessionInitMessage` response sent back to client\n\n**Request-Response Pattern:**\n```typescript\n// Client sends ChatRequest\n{\n  type: MessageType.ChatRequest,\n  id: \"uuid\",\n  sessionId: \"session-uuid\",\n  payload: {\n    query: \"Create a document about...\",\n    requestId: \"req-uuid\",\n    conversationId: \"conv-uuid\",\n    turnNumber: 1,\n    // ... optional: queryAnnotations, requestSource, scenarioType\n  }\n}\n\n// Server sends ChatResponseMessage (acknowledgment)\n{\n  type: MessageType.ChatResponse,\n  id: \"uuid\",\n  sessionId: \"session-uuid\",\n  requestId: \"req-uuid\",\n  payload: { success: true, conversationId: \"conv-uuid\" }\n}\n\n// Server streams TaskCompletionNotification messages\n{\n  type: MessageType.TaskCompletionNotification,\n  id: \"uuid\",\n  sessionId: \"session-uuid\",\n  payload: { ... artifact details ... }\n}\n```\n\n**File Upload/Download:**\n- `/upload` (POST) - Binary file upload with `?filePath=...` query param\n- `/download` (GET) - Binary file download with `?filePath=...` query param\n- Workspace path validation ensures files stay within agent output directory\n\n---\n\n### 11. FRAMEWORK & DEPENDENCY PATTERNS\n\n**No \"1JS\" Framework:**\n- Classic TypeScript monorepo (NO OneJourney framework, NO 1JS patterns)\n- Built on Node.js 24+ (Yarn 4.10.3 workspace)\n- Gulp 5.0 for build orchestration\n- Lage 2.14.15 for task parallelization\n\n**Core Dependencies:**\n```json\n{\n  \"@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk\": \"0.2.39\",      // Primary - Claude orchestration\n  \"@github/copilot-sdk\": \"0.1.30\",                 // Secondary - GHCP provider\n  \"express\": \"^4.x\",                              // API server\n  \"ws\": \"^8.x\",                                   // WebSocket server\n  \"typescript\": \"^5.9.3\",\n  \"jest\": \"^30.2.0\",                              // Testing\n  \"@augloop-tools/token-server\": \"^1.12.20\",      // Test client auth\n  \"playwright\": \"^latest\"                         // Browser automation (health checks)\n}\n```\n\n**Internal Workspace References** (`@officeagent/*`):\n- `@officeagent/core` - Agent base, logging, WebSocket routing\n- `@officeagent/orchestrator` - IOrchestrator abstraction\n- `@officeagent/api` - Express routes\n- `@officeagent/chain-of-thought` - CoT tracking\n- `@officeagent/grounding` - Enterprise/web search\n- `@officeagent/message-protocol` - Type definitions\n- `@officeagent/excel-headless` - Cloud Excel API\n- `@officeagent/html2pptx` - HTML → PPTX\n- `@officeagent/json-to-docx-ooxml` - JSON → Word\n- Agents use `workspace:^` version references\n\n---\n\n### 12. KEY DEVELOPMENT PATTERNS\n\n**Config Resolution:**\n```typescript\n// ConfigResolver.resolve(registry, flights, context)\n// Applies flights from settings manager, filters removed config items\n// Returns ResolvedAgentConfig with appliedFlights[], appliedFilters[]\n```\n\n**Settings Manager:**\n```typescript\n// OfficeAgentSettingsManager (core module)\nchangeGate(key: string): boolean;           // Feature flags\ngetBooleanSetting(key: string, defaultValue: boolean): boolean;\ngetIntSetting(key: string, defaultValue: number): number;\nsetFlight(flightKey: string, value: boolean): void;\ngetAgentId(): string;\n```\n\n**Workspace Manager:**\n```typescript\n// AgentWorkspaceManager - manages turn directories\ngetWorkspaceDir(): string;       // ~/.claude/\ngetOutputDir(): string;          // Current turn output\ngetLogsDir(): string;            // Logs for current turn\ngetCurrentTurnNumber(): number;\nisValidOutputDir(path: string): boolean;  // Security check\n```\n\n---\n\n### 13. SUMMARY: KEY ARCHITECTURAL PATTERNS\n\n| Component | Pattern | Location |\n|-----------|---------|----------|\n| **Agent Orchestration** | Factory pattern + registry | `/modules/orchestrator` |\n| **Provider Abstraction** | Inheritance + interface | `IOrchestrator` |\n| **Hook System** | Provider pattern + adapter | `/modules/core` + `/orchestrator/hooks` |\n| **Message Routing** | Type-based dispatch | `/modules/core/websocket` |\n| **Grounding** | Modular orchestrators | `/modules/grounding` |\n| **Configuration** | Registry + flights + filters | Agent `registry.ts` |\n| **Session Management** | Context objects + lifecycle | `SessionContext`, `TurnContext` |\n| **WebSocket Comm** | JSON messages + JSON-RPC 2.0 | `/modules/message-protocol` |\n| **Tool Interception** | Generic hooks → provider hooks | `claude-hook-adapter.ts` |\n| **Progress Tracking** | Async queue + file writes | `chain-of-thought` module |\n| **File I/O** | Workspace isolation | `AgentWorkspaceManager` |\n\n---\n\n### 14. \"COWORK\" / \"PROGRESSION\" REFERENCES\n\n- **No explicit \"cowork\" protocol** found\n- **Progression via**:\n  1. WebSocket `TaskCompletionNotification` messages (file generation, milestones)\n  2. Chain of Thought writes to `.claude/cot.jsonl` (streaming reasoning)\n  3. Hook callbacks during agentic execution (real-time tool tracking)\n- Think of it as: **Hooks → Progress → WebSocket Messages** (unidirectional push to client)\n\n---\n\nThis represents the complete architectural understanding of OfficeAgent. The system is a sophisticated multi-provider agent orchestration platform with streaming execution, rich hook systems, and WebSocket-based real-time communication—all without a formal \"1JS\" framework, built classically with TypeScript, Express, and modular workspace patterns."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a854b2eccbd6151db (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 101538\ntool_uses: 51\nduration_ms: 543958</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d982c5f4-98da-4461-b748-c7175dcade88","uuid":"c5feec35-38a8-4d60-8fed-d62985751f07","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the OfficeAgent codebase at C:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent. I need to understand:\n\n1. Read CLAUDE.md at the root if it exists\n2. The overall repo structure (ls the root, key directories)\n3. How agents are structured - look at a few agent directories under packages/ or agents/\n4. The orchestrator package - how does it expose IOrchestrator, ClaudeOrchestrator\n5. The API surface - how does the external API (port 6010) work? What endpoints exist?\n6. How AugLoop integration works - search for \"augloop\" or \"AugLoop\" references\n7. The hook system - how do hooks work for streaming CoT/progression\n8. How the frontend (if any) communicates with agents\n9. Any existing \"cowork\" references\n10. The 1JS framework references or patterns\n11. How the grounding pipeline works\n\nBe very thorough - read key files, not just list them. I need actual code patterns and interfaces.","agentId":"a854b2eccbd6151db","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive information. Let me create a detailed summary document for the user:\n\n## Comprehensive OfficeAgent Codebase Exploration Report\n\nI've conducted a thorough exploration of the OfficeAgent monorepo. Here's a detailed analysis of the architecture:\n\n---\n\n### 1. REPOSITORY STRUCTURE & OVERVIEW\n\n**Root Files:**\n- `/CLAUDE.md` - Project guidelines (no 1JS framework, uses Yarn 4.10.3 + Lage task runner)\n- `/package.json` - Monorepo with Yarn workspaces: `.devtools/*`, `modules/*`, `agents/*`\n- Key tools: Claude Agent SDK 0.2.39, GitHub Copilot SDK 0.1.30, AugLoop runtime client (test-client)\n\n**Directory Layout:**\n```\nagents/                    # 16 agent implementations\n├── create-agent/         # Main DOCX/PPTX/XLSX creation agent\n├── ppt-agent/            # PowerPoint specialized\n├── excel-agent/          # Excel specialized\n├── grounding-agent/      # Searches & grounding\n├── odsp-agent/           # SharePoint/OneDrive\n└── [11 others: gpt-create-agent, dw-*, workspace-agent, office-agent]\n\nmodules/                   # Shared libraries (@officeagent/*)\n├── api/                  # Express server (port 6010) + WebSocket\n├── core/                 # BaseAgent, SessionContext, HookRegistry, logging\n├── orchestrator/         # IOrchestrator abstraction (claude + ghcp providers)\n├── chain-of-thought/     # Progress/CoT tracking & streaming\n├── grounding/            # Enterprise search, web search, image search\n├── message-protocol/     # WebSocket message types, RequestContext\n├── excel-headless/       # Cloud Excel via headless service\n├── html2pptx/            # HTML → PPTX conversion\n├── json-to-docx-ooxml/   # JSON → OOXML (Word) generation\n├── mcp-proxy/            # MCP tool integration\n└── [10+ others]\n\n.devtools/                 # Development tools\n├── cli/                  # oagent CLI tool\n├── test-client/          # Augloop test client\n├── e2e-tests/            # End-to-end testing\n└── launcher/             # Container orchestration\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. CLAUDE.md AT ROOT\n\nThe root `CLAUDE.md` provides critical context:\n- **Critical**: Use **PowerShell** for `yarn`, `oagent`, `gulp` commands (Bash will fail)\n- File searching (grep, find) works in any shell\n- All config uses `OAGENT_` prefix (`OAGENT_AGENTID`, `OAGENT_FLIGHTS`)\n- Default API: `http://localhost:6010`\n- Agents register skills, flights, filters in `src/registry.ts`\n- Logging rule: **NEVER include user data in `logInfo`/`logWarn`/`logError`** (telemetry), use `logDebug` for local data\n- Agent-specific CLAUDE.md files exist for each area (CLAUDE_EXCEL.md, CLAUDE_POWERPOINT.md, CLAUDE_WORD.md)\n\n---\n\n### 3. ORCHESTRATOR PACKAGE - IOrchestrator & ClaudeOrchestrator\n\n**Location:** `/modules/orchestrator`\n\n**Core Interface:**\n```typescript\n// IOrchestrator - unified abstraction for all AI providers\ninterface IOrchestrator {\n  run(request: OrchestratorRequest): Promise<OrchestratorResult>;\n  runStream(request: OrchestratorRequest): AsyncIterable<OrchestratorMessage>;\n  interrupt(): Promise<void>;\n}\n\n// OrchestratorRequest - what agents send to the orchestrator\ninterface OrchestratorRequest {\n  prompt: string;\n  userContext?: string;           // Injected before prompt\n  systemPrompt?: string;\n  model?: string;                 // e.g., 'claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929'\n  maxTurns?: number;\n  reasoningEffort?: 'low' | 'medium' | 'high' | 'max' | 'xhigh';\n  allowedTools?: string[];        // Tool allowlist\n  disallowedTools?: string[];     // Tool blocklist\n  toolDefinitions?: unknown[];    // For providers like GHCP\n  cwd?: string;\n  env?: Record<string, string>;\n  abortController?: AbortController;\n  hooks?: OrchestratorHooks;      // Batch mode hooks (onMessage, onError, onPre/PostToolUse)\n  toolHooks?: GenericToolHooks;   // Provider-agnostic tool interception hooks\n  sessionId?: string;             // For resuming conversations\n  providerOptions?: Record<string, unknown>;  // Provider-specific (Claude: `continue`, `stderr`, `permissionMode`)\n}\n\n// OrchestratorMessage - normalized output for all providers\ninterface OrchestratorMessage {\n  type: 'assistant' | 'tool_use' | 'tool_result' | 'thinking' | 'system' | 'result' | 'progress';\n  content?: string;\n  toolName?: string;\n  toolInput?: unknown;\n  result?: OrchestratorResult;    // Embedded when type === 'result'\n  durationMs?: number;\n  sessionId?: string;\n  raw?: unknown;                  // Provider-specific raw data\n}\n\n// OrchestratorResult - final output\ninterface OrchestratorResult {\n  content: string;\n  status: 'completed' | 'exhausted' | 'failed' | 'aborted';\n  sessionId?: string;\n  error?: string;\n  usage?: OrchestratorUsage;      // Metrics: inputTokens, outputTokens, costUsd, durationMs, turnCount\n  metadata?: Record<string, unknown>;\n}\n```\n\n**Provider Pattern:**\n- `/providers/base-orchestrator.ts` - Abstract base class; providers override `runStream()` and `interrupt()`\n- `/providers/claude-orchestrator.ts` - Claude Agent SDK adapter\n- `/providers/ghcp-orchestrator.ts` - GitHub Copilot SDK adapter (lazy-loaded)\n- Factory: `createOrchestrator('claude' | 'ghcp')` - registry-based instantiation\n\n**Hook System:**\n```typescript\n// Generic tool hooks (provider-agnostic)\ninterface GenericToolHooks {\n  preToolUse?: PreToolUseHook[];       // (toolName, input) → {continue, modifiedInput?, reason?}\n  postToolUse?: PostToolUseHook[];     // (toolName, output) → {continue, modifiedOutput?}\n  onSessionStart?: SessionHook[];\n  onSessionEnd?: SessionHook[];\n}\n```\n\n**Hook Adapter:**\n- `/hooks/claude-hook-adapter.ts` - `toClaudeHooks()` & `mergeWithClaudeHooks()` translate GenericToolHooks → Claude SDK format\n- Allows hook providers (ppt-hooks, word-hooks, excel-hooks) to be written once, work with all orchestrators\n\n---\n\n### 4. API SURFACE (Port 6010)\n\n**Location:** `/modules/api/src`\n\n**Key Endpoints:**\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |\n|----------|--------|---------|\n| `/ping` | GET | Health check (responds \"pong\") |\n| `/health` | GET | Extended health status |\n| `/test` | GET | Deep health check (Chromium headless test) |\n| `/generateDocument` | POST | Main document generation (HTTP request) |\n| `/download` | GET | File download from workspace |\n| `/upload` | POST | Binary file upload (application/octet-stream) |\n| `/logs` | GET | Fetch & clear log entries |\n| `/ws` | WebSocket | Primary message channel (JSON message + JSON-RPC 2.0) |\n\n**WebSocket Message Types:**\n- `ChatRequest` - Initiate document generation\n- `ChatResponse` - Acknowledgment\n- `TaskCompletionNotification` - Progress updates\n- `MessageAnnotation` - Query metadata (entities, filters)\n- `AgentStateRequest/Response` - State management\n- `ChatHistoryRequest/Response` - History queries\n\n**Internal Port:** 6011 (for internal handler communication, see `/routes-internal.ts`)\n\n**Request Flow (HTTP `/generateDocument`):**\n1. Client POSTs with: `userQuery`, `groundingContent`, `conversationId`, `queryAnnotations`, `webSearch`, `enterpriseSearch`, etc.\n2. Server generates `requestId` if missing, checks conversation not busy\n3. Loads agent from `AgentRegistry.getAgent(agentId)`\n4. Calls `agent.run(processedQuery, requestContext, turnNumber)`\n5. Returns: `{success, filename, filePath, requestId, conversationId}` or 202 (async)\n\n**WebSocket Flow (streamlined via `/ws`):**\n- Client connects to `/ws` (WebSocket upgrade on port 6010)\n- Sends `SessionInitMessage` → server initializes agent context\n- Sends `AgentRequestMessage` (type: ChatRequest) → routed to agent handler\n- Server streams progress via `TaskCompletionNotification`, CoT updates\n- Final response as `ChatResponseMessage`\n\n---\n\n### 5. HOW AGENTS ARE STRUCTURED\n\n**Example: CreateAgent** (`/agents/create-agent`)\n\n**Key Files:**\n```\nsrc/\n  create-agent.ts          # Main class extending BaseAgent\n  registry.ts              # AgentRegistryConfig: versions, flights, filters, skills, subagents\n  types.ts                 # AgentType enum (WordAgent, ExcelAgent, PowerPointAgent)\n  constants.ts             # Flight keys, artifact type constants\n  hooks/\n    base-hooks.ts          # BaseHooksProvider - shared hooks (perf tracking, CoT)\n    excel-hooks.ts         # ExcelHooksProvider - Excel-specific hooks\n    ppt-hooks.ts           # PowerPointHooksProvider\n    word-hooks.ts          # WordHooksProvider\n    file-observer-hooks.ts # File system monitoring\n  services/\n    performance-tracker-service.ts    # Hook-based perf metrics\n    chat-history-service.ts           # Chat history persistence\n    agent-state-service.ts            # Agent state management\n    file-watcher.ts                   # Monitor output directory changes\n    websocket-messenger.ts            # Send messages to clients\n  handlers/\n    agent-request-handler.ts          # JSON-RPC & legacy request handling\n    sydney-request-parser.ts          # AugLoop message parsing\n  prompts/<version>/\n    system-prompt.md                  # EJS template for system prompt\n    rai.md                            # Responsible AI guidelines\n    agent-capabilities/               # Per-type descriptions\n    skills/                           # Skill definitions (xlsx/, pptx/, docx/, etc.)\n    subagents/                        # Sub-agent prompts (markdown with YAML frontmatter)\n    scripts/                          # Runtime scripts deployed to workspace\n    overwrites/                       # Flight-conditional prompt replacements\n```\n\n**CreateAgent Pattern:**\n```typescript\nexport class CreateAgent extends BaseAgent {\n  private hookRegistry: HookRegistry;  // Manages hook providers for different agents\n  private requestInterceptors?: RequestInterceptors;\n  private context?: SessionContext;\n\n  constructor() {\n    super(agentRegistry);  // Pass AgentRegistryConfig\n    this.hookRegistry = new HookRegistry();\n    this.hookRegistry.register('base', new BaseHooksProvider());\n    this.hookRegistry.register(AgentType.WordAgent, new WordHooksProvider());\n    this.hookRegistry.register(AgentType.ExcelAgent, new ExcelHooksProvider());\n    this.hookRegistry.register(AgentType.PowerPointAgent, new PowerPointHooksProvider());\n  }\n\n  async initialize(context: SessionContext): Promise<void> {\n    this.resolveConfig(context);  // Apply flights & filters from settings manager\n    this.context = context;\n    // Register WebSocket handlers, initialize services\n    context.wsRouter.registerHandler(MessageType.ChatRequest, this.handleChatRequest.bind(this));\n    // Initialize JSON-RPC if enabled\n    if (this.jsonRpcEnabled) {\n      context.wsRouter.getJsonRpcRouter().registerRequestHandler(JsonRpcMethod.MessageSend, ...);\n    }\n  }\n\n  async run(userQuery: string, requestContext: RequestContext, turnNumber?: number): Promise<void> {\n    // Orchestrate document generation\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Registry Configuration** (`registry.ts` pattern):\n```typescript\nexport const agentRegistry: AgentRegistryConfig = {\n  id: 'create-agent',\n  name: 'Create Agent',\n  packageName: '@officeagent/create-agent',\n  defaultVersion: '1.0.0',\n  versions: [\n    {\n      version: '1.0.0',\n      model: 'claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929',\n      maxThinkingTokens: 1024,\n      maxTurns: 2000,\n      systemPrompt: './system-prompt.md',\n      allowedTools: ['Read', 'Write', 'Edit', 'Bash', 'Task', 'Skill', ...],\n      skills: ['docx', 'pptx', 'xlsx', 'image-search', ...],\n      subagents: ['pptx-html-creator-validator', 'docx-page-subagent', ...],\n      scripts: ['send-clarification-config.js'],\n      intentDetectionDir: ['CLARIFICATION.md', 'CHAT_REPLY.md', ...],\n    },\n    { version: '1.1.0', ... },  // New version with pipeline upgrades\n  ],\n  flights: [  // Flight-based config overrides\n    { flightKey: 'OfficeAgent.EnableCreateAgent@1.1.0', applicableVersions: ['1.1.0'], config: {...} },\n  ],\n  filters: [  // Filter rules\n    { filterKey: 'disableWebSearch', skills: ['web-search', 'web-fetch'] },\n  ],\n};\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. HOOK SYSTEM - STREAMING CoT & PROGRESSION\n\n**Location:** `/modules/chain-of-thought` + `/modules/core/src/agent/claude-hooks.ts`\n\n**Hook Provider Pattern:**\n```typescript\n// HookProvider - factory for creating hooks\nexport interface HookProvider {\n  createHooks(context: SessionContext, turnContext?: TurnContext): AgentHooks;\n}\n\nexport interface AgentHooks {\n  claude: Options['hooks'];  // Claude SDK hook structure\n  startTurn?: (turnContext: TurnContext) => Promise<void>;  // Called at turn start\n  preFileWatcherStart?: () => Promise<void>;\n}\n\n// HookRegistry - manages multiple hook providers\nexport class HookRegistry {\n  register(key: string, provider: HookProvider): void { ... }\n  getHooks(key: string, context: SessionContext, turnContext?: TurnContext): AgentHooks { ... }\n}\n```\n\n**Chain of Thought (CoT) System:**\n```typescript\n// Types from chain-of-thought/src/types.ts\ninterface ChainOfThoughtMessage {\n  type: string;  // 'assistant' | 'result'\n  message?: { content?: ChainOfThoughtContentBlock[] };\n  subtype?: string;  // 'success', 'error_max_turns', etc.\n  result?: string;\n  parent_tool_use_id?: string | null;  // Identifies sub-agent messages\n}\n\n// Manager API\ninitChainOfThought(outputDir, logDir, workspaceDir, locale, flights?, contentNotifier?);\ntrackChainOfThought(message: ChainOfThoughtMessage): Promise<void>;  // Queue message for processing\ncloseChainOfThought(): Promise<void>;  // Wait for queue completion, flush\n\n// CoT is written to `.claude/cot.jsonl` in turn directory\n// Messages are queued async, processed via FileHandler + QueueManager\n// Flights: useContentHandler, sendOnlyNewUpdates, useEnhancedHeuristics, requireToolUseForQueueFallback\n```\n\n**Example Hook (BaseHooksProvider):**\n```typescript\n// Performance tracking hook - fired before/after each tool use\nconst perfHooks = createPerfTrackingHooks(sessionId, settingsManager);\n\nconst claudeHooks: Options['hooks'] = {\n  PreToolUse: [{ hooks: [perfHooks.PreToolUse] }],\n  PostToolUse: [{ hooks: [perfHooks.PostToolUse] }],\n  SessionStart: [{ hooks: [perfHooks.SessionStart] }],\n  SessionEnd: [{ hooks: [perfHooks.SessionEnd] }],\n};\n\n// startTurn hook - called at beginning of each turn\nstartTurn: async (turnContext: TurnContext) => {\n  const turnNumber = turnContext.workspaceManager.getCurrentTurnNumber();\n  logInfo(..., `[BaseHooks] Turn ${turnNumber} started`);\n  // Copy entityMap from previous turn, fetch user attachments, etc.\n}\n```\n\n**Progression/Streaming:**\n- Hooks are Claude SDK hooks (`Options['hooks']` with PreToolUse, PostToolUse callbacks)\n- They execute in-band during agentic turns\n- CoT is tracked separately via `trackChainOfThought()` → async queued writes to `.claude/cot.jsonl`\n- WebSocket messenger sends `TaskCompletionNotification` & progress updates to client\n- No explicit \"cowork\" protocol; progression sent via individual WebSocket messages\n\n---\n\n### 7. GROUNDING PIPELINE\n\n**Location:** `/modules/grounding`\n\n**Grounding Service Types:**\n```typescript\n// Request to grounding service\ninterface GroundingHttpRequest {\n  query: string;\n  configs?: { enterpriseSearch?: boolean, webSearch?: boolean };\n  conversationId?: string;\n  sessionId?: string;\n  requestId?: string;\n  queryAnnotations?: IQueryAnnotation[];  // User-attached entities\n}\n\n// Response from grounding service\ninterface GroundingHttpResponse {\n  status: 'completed' | 'failed';\n  groundingContent: string;              // Formatted markdown\n  metadata?: { requestId, durationMs, sourcesUsed };\n  error?: string;\n}\n\n// HTTP Server (default port 7010)\nclass GroundingHttpServer { ... }  // Runs search orchestration\n\n// Client for internal agent-to-agent calls\nclass GroundingClient { ... }  // Calls local grounding service\n```\n\n**Grounding Modules:**\n- `enterprise/` - Enterprise search via orchestration (fetch, search, user-context orchestrators)\n- `images/` - Image search integration\n- `user-attachment/` - Fetch user-attached content (from provisioned files)\n- `shared/` - Shared utilities\n\n**parseGroundingContent():**\n```typescript\n// Parses grounding.md format into clarification questions, message annotations, etc.\nconst groundingContentParsed = parseGroundingContent(groundingContent);\n// Returns structured questions, annotations, and text for injection into user query\n```\n\n**Enterprise Search Orchestration:**\n- **Fetch Orchestrator** - Retrieves files from SharePoint/OneDrive\n- **Search Orchestrator** - Searches enterprise knowledge\n- **User Context Orchestrator** - Builds user profile context\n- Post-processors format results into markdown for injection\n\n---\n\n### 8. AUGLOOP INTEGRATION\n\n**Location:** `/.devtools/test-client/src/augloop-client.ts`\n\n**What is AugLoop?**\n- Microsoft's intelligent document collaboration platform\n- `@augloop/runtime-client` - Client SDK for annotations & operations\n- Test client uses it for UI annotation callbacks\n\n**AugLoopClient Pattern:**\n```typescript\nclass AugLoopClient {\n  async initialize(environment: TokenEnvironment, flights?: string): Promise<void> {\n    const runtime = createRuntime();\n    runtime?.init(endpointUrl, {\n      appName: 'OfficeAgent',\n      appPlatform: 'TestClient',\n      flights,\n      uiLanguage: 'en-US',\n    }, {\n      onAnnotationResult: (op: IOperation) => { ... }  // Callback when annotation completes\n    });\n  }\n  // Used for testing agent against AugLoop backend\n}\n```\n\n**Endpoints by Environment:**\n- Dev: `http://localhost:11040`\n- Prod: `https://augloop.svc.cloud.microsoft`\n- Gov: `https://augloop.gov.online.office365.us`\n- Gallatin: `https://augloop.microsoftonline.cn`\n\n**Integration points:**\n- Used in test-client only (not production agents)\n- Test client registers annotation callbacks, validates operations\n\n---\n\n### 9. MESSAGE PROTOCOL & WebSocket ROUTING\n\n**Location:** `/modules/message-protocol`\n\n**Core Types:**\n```typescript\n// Base message schema\ninterface Schema {\n  type: MessageType;\n  id: string;\n}\n\ninterface Message<T = unknown> extends Schema {\n  sessionId: string;\n  payload: T;\n}\n\ninterface ResponseMessage<T = unknown> extends Message<T> {\n  requestId: string;\n}\n\n// Scenario & grounding toggles\nenum ScenarioType { Consumer = 'consumer', Enterprise = 'enterprise' }\ninterface IGroundingSourceToggles {\n  webSearch: boolean;\n  enterpriseSearch: boolean;\n}\n\n// Client metadata\ninterface ClientMetadata {\n  agentName?: string;\n  userEmail?: string;\n  // ... platform-specific fields\n}\n```\n\n**WebSocket Router:**\n```typescript\n// modules/core/src/websocket/router.ts\nexport class WebSocketRouter {\n  registerHandler(messageType: string, handler: MessageHandler): void { ... }\n  async routeMessage(rawMessage: string, ws: WebSocket): Promise<void> {\n    // Parse JSON, check for JSON-RPC 2.0 (delegate to jsonRpcRouter)\n    // else route by message.type to registered handler\n  }\n  getJsonRpcRouter(): JsonRpcRouter { ... }\n}\n\n// Message handler signature\ntype MessageHandler = (message: any, ws: WebSocket) => boolean | Promise<boolean>;\n```\n\n**JSON-RPC 2.0 Support:**\n- `isJsonRpcMessage(message)` - checks for `jsonrpc: \"2.0\"` + `method`\n- `JsonRpcRouter` - handles `method`, `id`, `params` format\n- Enables unified request-response pattern for message types\n\n---\n\n### 10. FRONTEND COMMUNICATION PATTERNS\n\n**Session Initialization Flow:**\n1. Client connects WebSocket to `/ws`\n2. Sends `SessionInitMessage` with client metadata, grounding toggles, MCP configs\n3. Server calls `registerSessionInitHandler()` → initializes agents in `AgentRegistry`\n4. Agent's `initialize(context: SessionContext)` called\n5. `SessionInitMessage` response sent back to client\n\n**Request-Response Pattern:**\n```typescript\n// Client sends ChatRequest\n{\n  type: MessageType.ChatRequest,\n  id: \"uuid\",\n  sessionId: \"session-uuid\",\n  payload: {\n    query: \"Create a document about...\",\n    requestId: \"req-uuid\",\n    conversationId: \"conv-uuid\",\n    turnNumber: 1,\n    // ... optional: queryAnnotations, requestSource, scenarioType\n  }\n}\n\n// Server sends ChatResponseMessage (acknowledgment)\n{\n  type: MessageType.ChatResponse,\n  id: \"uuid\",\n  sessionId: \"session-uuid\",\n  requestId: \"req-uuid\",\n  payload: { success: true, conversationId: \"conv-uuid\" }\n}\n\n// Server streams TaskCompletionNotification messages\n{\n  type: MessageType.TaskCompletionNotification,\n  id: \"uuid\",\n  sessionId: \"session-uuid\",\n  payload: { ... artifact details ... }\n}\n```\n\n**File Upload/Download:**\n- `/upload` (POST) - Binary file upload with `?filePath=...` query param\n- `/download` (GET) - Binary file download with `?filePath=...` query param\n- Workspace path validation ensures files stay within agent output directory\n\n---\n\n### 11. FRAMEWORK & DEPENDENCY PATTERNS\n\n**No \"1JS\" Framework:**\n- Classic TypeScript monorepo (NO OneJourney framework, NO 1JS patterns)\n- Built on Node.js 24+ (Yarn 4.10.3 workspace)\n- Gulp 5.0 for build orchestration\n- Lage 2.14.15 for task parallelization\n\n**Core Dependencies:**\n```json\n{\n  \"@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk\": \"0.2.39\",      // Primary - Claude orchestration\n  \"@github/copilot-sdk\": \"0.1.30\",                 // Secondary - GHCP provider\n  \"express\": \"^4.x\",                              // API server\n  \"ws\": \"^8.x\",                                   // WebSocket server\n  \"typescript\": \"^5.9.3\",\n  \"jest\": \"^30.2.0\",                              // Testing\n  \"@augloop-tools/token-server\": \"^1.12.20\",      // Test client auth\n  \"playwright\": \"^latest\"                         // Browser automation (health checks)\n}\n```\n\n**Internal Workspace References** (`@officeagent/*`):\n- `@officeagent/core` - Agent base, logging, WebSocket routing\n- `@officeagent/orchestrator` - IOrchestrator abstraction\n- `@officeagent/api` - Express routes\n- `@officeagent/chain-of-thought` - CoT tracking\n- `@officeagent/grounding` - Enterprise/web search\n- `@officeagent/message-protocol` - Type definitions\n- `@officeagent/excel-headless` - Cloud Excel API\n- `@officeagent/html2pptx` - HTML → PPTX\n- `@officeagent/json-to-docx-ooxml` - JSON → Word\n- Agents use `workspace:^` version references\n\n---\n\n### 12. KEY DEVELOPMENT PATTERNS\n\n**Config Resolution:**\n```typescript\n// ConfigResolver.resolve(registry, flights, context)\n// Applies flights from settings manager, filters removed config items\n// Returns ResolvedAgentConfig with appliedFlights[], appliedFilters[]\n```\n\n**Settings Manager:**\n```typescript\n// OfficeAgentSettingsManager (core module)\nchangeGate(key: string): boolean;           // Feature flags\ngetBooleanSetting(key: string, defaultValue: boolean): boolean;\ngetIntSetting(key: string, defaultValue: number): number;\nsetFlight(flightKey: string, value: boolean): void;\ngetAgentId(): string;\n```\n\n**Workspace Manager:**\n```typescript\n// AgentWorkspaceManager - manages turn directories\ngetWorkspaceDir(): string;       // ~/.claude/\ngetOutputDir(): string;          // Current turn output\ngetLogsDir(): string;            // Logs for current turn\ngetCurrentTurnNumber(): number;\nisValidOutputDir(path: string): boolean;  // Security check\n```\n\n---\n\n### 13. SUMMARY: KEY ARCHITECTURAL PATTERNS\n\n| Component | Pattern | Location |\n|-----------|---------|----------|\n| **Agent Orchestration** | Factory pattern + registry | `/modules/orchestrator` |\n| **Provider Abstraction** | Inheritance + interface | `IOrchestrator` |\n| **Hook System** | Provider pattern + adapter | `/modules/core` + `/orchestrator/hooks` |\n| **Message Routing** | Type-based dispatch | `/modules/core/websocket` |\n| **Grounding** | Modular orchestrators | `/modules/grounding` |\n| **Configuration** | Registry + flights + filters | Agent `registry.ts` |\n| **Session Management** | Context objects + lifecycle | `SessionContext`, `TurnContext` |\n| **WebSocket Comm** | JSON messages + JSON-RPC 2.0 | `/modules/message-protocol` |\n| **Tool Interception** | Generic hooks → provider hooks | `claude-hook-adapter.ts` |\n| **Progress Tracking** | Async queue + file writes | `chain-of-thought` module |\n| **File I/O** | Workspace isolation | `AgentWorkspaceManager` |\n\n---\n\n### 14. \"COWORK\" / \"PROGRESSION\" REFERENCES\n\n- **No explicit \"cowork\" protocol** found\n- **Progression via**:\n  1. WebSocket `TaskCompletionNotification` messages (file generation, milestones)\n  2. Chain of Thought writes to `.claude/cot.jsonl` (streaming reasoning)\n  3. Hook callbacks during agentic execution (real-time tool tracking)\n- Think of it as: **Hooks → Progress → WebSocket Messages** (unidirectional push to client)\n\n---\n\nThis represents the complete architectural understanding of OfficeAgent. The system is a sophisticated multi-provider agent orchestration platform with streaming execution, rich hook systems, and WebSocket-based real-time communication—all without a formal \"1JS\" framework, built classically with TypeScript, Express, and modular workspace patterns."}],"totalDurationMs":543958,"totalTokens":101538,"totalToolUseCount":51,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2132,"cache_read_input_tokens":92213,"output_tokens":7192,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2132},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
